    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the PR. Let me summarize 
what I\'ve found:\n\n**What the PR does:**\n- Redesigns UI container components 
(UIPanel, UIDialog, UIToast, UIAlert) to align with PRD-004 and the UI style gui
de\n- Adds infrastructure like `types.ts`, `utils.ts` improvements (toast tweens
, colorToHex, etc.)\n- Adds tests for the redesigned components\n- Updates docum
entation (03-component.md, ui-components.md, agent-design-guide.md, 01-foundatio
n.md)\n- Adds design deliverables in `designs/issue-19/`\n\n**Key issues found:*
*\n\n1. **Blocking - No `export default` removed from apps files**: The PR descr
iption mentions removing `export default` (F-11), but looking at the diffs, the 
apps/phaser3 files still have `export default` at the bottom for some files. Wai
t, let me re-check. The UIButton diff shows:\n```\n-export default UIButton;\n``
`\nwas REMOVED. Let me verify for other files.\n\nActually, looking at the UIBut
ton diff, it shows `export default UIButton;` was removed. Good.\nFor UIDialog, 
I didn\'t see the end of the diff. Let me check.\nFor UIPanel, I didn\'t see the
end of the diff either.\nFor UIAlert, I need to check.\nFor UIToast, I need to c
heck.\n\nLet me grep for export default in the changed files.\n\n2. **Major - `U
IAlert.getTypeColor(\'warning\')` test in designs/issue-19 expects `UITheme.gold
Brown` instead of `UITheme.warning`**: This is inconsistent with PRD-004 and the
updated component spec. The apps version was fixed but the design version still 
has the bug.\n\n3. **Major - Potential event listener leak in UIButton.setTextur
e()**: When `setTexture()` is called, it calls `setupInteraction()` again. But w
ait - the old background is destroyed. The listeners are on the background, so t
hey should be gone. But what about the container? Let me re-check. Actually, `se
tupInteraction()` sets listeners on `this.background`. When `this.background` is
destroyed and replaced, the old listeners go with it. So calling `setupInteracti
on()` again is fine. BUT - `setTexture()` does `this.remove(this.label); this.ad
d(this.label);` which is fine. However, it doesn\'t handle the case where `setTe
xture()` is called while the button is disabled. The new background will have `s
etInteractive({ useHandCursor: true })` called on it, which would incorrectly ma
ke it interactive even if disabled. Actually, looking at `setupInteraction()`, a
t the end it checks:\n```typescript\nif (this.config.isDisabled) {\n  target.dis
ableInteractive();\n  this.setAlpha(0.5);\n}\n```\nSo if the button is disabled,
it will correctly disable interactive again. OK, this is handled.\n\nWait, but t
here\'s another issue. `setTexture()` does:\n```typescript\nthis.background.dest
roy();\nthis.createBackground();\nthis.remove(this.label);\nthis.add(this.label)
